## Risk pattern: stacking

The most common way the doctrine breaks is stacking — committing to
multiple things at once instead of one at a time.

Signals:
- New Claude Code prompts being written before the current one is shipped
- More than two major projects active at once
- Excitement about a new idea that would delay the core thing
- "Let me just also..." appearing in the same session as another fix

When stacking happens, name it directly. "I'm stacking. Cutting two
things." Pick from the cut list. Get back to one thing at a time.

