## OAuth and integrations

Integrations are where most production bugs hide because they involve
state we don't fully control (Google's OAuth, Stripe's billing, Supabase's
auth).

Rules specific to integrations:
- Test as multiple users with separate browser profiles. Cross-account
  state in one browser session causes corruption.
- After every OAuth connect, verify the saved tokens match the expected
  user (check the database directly).
- Validate critical fields at save time. If a refresh_token didn't come
  back, fail loudly. Don't save a half-broken connection.
- Surface broken connections in the UI. Silent failures are the worst
  kind of bug because users don't know to fix them.
- For any integration, check `console.<provider>.com` periodically
  for spend, errors, rate limits.

