## What we'd cut before we cut each other

The single most important rule, the one that supersedes all others:

**We cut the business before we cut each other.**

If the business is hurting the marriage, we shrink the business.
If the business is hurting the kids, we pause the business.
If the business is hurting our souls, we walk away from the business.

We built this together. We can unbuild it together. No outcome is
worth losing what we actually built this for.

The doctrine exists in service of building Trellis. The marriage,
the family, and our wellbeing exist before the doctrine.

If applying the doctrine becomes itself another stack on the pile,
the doctrine is wrong and we revise it.

---

## How this doctrine evolves

This is a living document. When we learn something new, we update it.
When a rule turns out to be wrong, we change it.

Rules for edits:
- Major changes discussed between Remi and Kendra first
- Small additions (new examples, clarifications) just commit
- When you violate a rule, document the violation and what you learned

The doctrine is not a constitution. It's a working set of rules we've
chosen to operate by because we've learned they make us more effective
and our product more trustworthy.

